Found 125 linter issues in the Supabase project:

INFO 1: RLS Enabled No Policy
  Level: INFO
  Description: Detects cases where row level security (RLS) has been enabled on a table but no RLS policies have been created.
  Categories: SECURITY
  How to fix (visit the link to see what to do!): https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/database-linter?lint=0008_rls_enabled_no_policy

WARN 2: RLS Policy Always True
  Level: WARN
  Description: Detects RLS policies that use overly permissive expressions like \`USING (true)\` or \`WITH CHECK (true)\` for UPDATE, DELETE, or INSERT operations. SELECT policies with \`USING (true)\` are intentionally excluded as this pattern is often used deliberately for public read access.
  Categories: SECURITY
  How to fix (visit the link to see what to do!): https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/database-linter?lint=0024_permissive_rls_policy

WARN 3: RLS Policy Always True
  Level: WARN
